23/06/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Kosumi on Wednesday (22 June) was saluted by the province's newly formed ceremonial guard unit, which will greet foreign dignitaries visiting the province. 
The event took place at the headquarters of the Kosovo Protection Corps (KPC).
Also Wednesday, Oliver Ivanovic, a Kosovo Serb leader, urged Belgrade to support Serb participation in Kosovo's provisional institutions. 
In letters sent to senior Serbian and Serbia-Montenegro officials, Ivanovic said such participation is the only way to protect Serb interests. 
(Politika - 23/06/05; Reuters, B92 - 22/06/05)
